title: Grateful Dead Live at Henry J. Kaiser Convention Center on 1987-03-01
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave (24bit output) > TLH > FLAC 2448 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 03/2016
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Grey-> Little Red Rooster, Peggy-O, Me & My Uncle, Mexicali Blues, When Push Comes To Shove, It's All Over Now, Row Jimmy-> Let It Grow

Set 2

Hell In A Bucket-> Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Samson & Delilah, Black Muddy River-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Space-> The Other One-> Black Peter-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text: Nice recording here Love the new uploads, any chance you or someone else reading this could put up the show from summer of 1982 the Keil on 8 4 1982 in audience please

BEST SHOW EVER Or at least the best show of the 250 i have been to.
or at least the best let it grow.
the energy coming from the band was unbelievable.
